Your task is to build an AI agent that allows a user to query and interact with their personal knowledge base. The agent should ingest user-provided documents, index them using embeddings, and retrieve relevant context to answer questions. The goal is to evaluate your ability to build retrieval-augmented AI systems that organize and surface insights from personal information sources while providing a high-quality conversational AI interface.


Objective
Create an agent application that:

Ingests user documents into a personal knowledge base
Builds an embedding-based retrieval system
Accepts natural language questions about stored documents
Retrieves relevant information from the knowledge base
Generates contextual answers grounded in the user's documents

Requirements
Use either LangChain or Mastra as your agent framework.
Include a UI with best-practices in AI UX.
Your app must allow users to upload and ingest documents into their personal knowledge base, supported formats should include PDF, Markdown, text files, scanned documents and optionally web pages.
Your app should maintain a history of previously uploaded document collections and previous conversations, and allow switching between them.
Previously uploaded knowledge bases can be refreshed or re-indexed.
Answers returned from the agent should include references to the retrieved documents.
The agent should support conversational queries where follow-up questions can rely on previous context.
You must use environment variables for all API keys.
Use the OPENROUTER_API_KEY for the API key.
Use the MODEL_NAME env variable for the model name.
You must include an .env.example file.
Include clear documentation in a top-level README.md explaining how to set up and run the Agent UI and backend.
There will be bonus points for including a CLI.
